Industries: Apps, Audio, Consumer Electronics, Electronics, iOS, Mobile Apps, Music, Wireless
Description: EKKO Audio offers HUB, a device that enables its users to share audio with multiple users in real time.
Full Description: HUB | The first Hi-Fi, Wi-Fi hub for headphones and speakers Share hi-fi audio to multiple users for a real-time, wireless listening experience unlike anything you’ve heard. Introducing HUB by ekko, the first Hi-Fi, Wi-Fi audio hub for headphones and speakers. It lets you instantly share wireless audio with multiple simultaneous listeners using any earbuds, headphones or powered speakers. This is the wireless sound experience you’ve been waiting for. Share real-time wireless audio with 4+ users A revolutionary approach to group listening, HUB uses ultra-low latency Wi-Fi technology to stream real-time audio to multiple listeners. Its audiophile-grade quality is enough to satisfy the needs of the most demanding listeners, while its design is simple enough for the whole family to enjoy. It’s a perfect solution for music, movies, games, and more.   Individual wireless receivers In addition to the app, each receiver incorporates volume and mute functions for simple control over each user’s listening experience. Hear what you’ve been missing   HUB's high-resolution 96kHz / 24-bit audio quality and individual user equalizer settings allows each listener to personalize their own listening experience. Listen loud? Prefer softer sound? Adjust your settings to suit your preference without interrupting anyone else’s. Stream from any source Connect the base station to any audio source, and built-in Wi-Fi instantly streams audio to one or more portable wireless receivers. Designed for single or multiple users Connect any pair of earbuds, headphones or speakers to one of ekko’s rechargeable wireless sound pucks. Support for 4+ simultaneous users. Control everything from one app Mobile app lets you customize your listening experience. Fine-tune equalizer settings, set volume safety limits, manage security features like encryption and password protection, access your favorite streaming music services, and more. Adjustable safe volume limits Volume safety limits help parents to ensure safe listening for kids. Adjust maximum volume levels, or manage each receiver’s volume in real-time using the mobile app. Simple multi-room audio In addition to headphones, HUB can connect to any powered speakers or stereo system, allowing you to set up a wireless multi-zone audio system in seconds. Control each zone’s volume and equalizer settings using the mobile app. Rechargeable sound pucks are a perfect solution for temporary setups like parties, while an optional individual charging accessory will be available for semi-permanent installations. Compatible with everything Easily play audio from any hardwired source via HUB’s RCA / AUX and optical audio inputs, and wirelessly via Airplay/DLNA. Additionally, ekko allows users to stream from mobile devices using their favorite streaming media apps, or directly from their Windows or Mac devices. Beautifully functional design HUB by ekko was thoughtfully designed to look great in any setting. Currently available in two color choices: black or silver. Wireless charging The HUB base station connects directly to an AC power outlet and charges the sound pucks via wireless induction charging. The sound pucks are simply placed on the base unit to recharge. hub mini: 2-user model HUB will come in two versions: the standard 4-user model and the 2-user HUB mini, ideal for smaller groups. Prototyping & Development Over the past year, the ekko Audio team has worked closely with our design and engineering partners to bring HUB from a humble napkin sketch to a sleek, finalized industrial design, to working proof-of-concept prototypes. Building on what we learned in testing, we began drafting plans and specifications for the consumer-ready device, which brings us to where we are today.
Industry Groups: Apps, Consumer Electronics, Hardware, Media and Entertainment, Mobile, Music and Audio, Platforms, Software
Founders: Frank Elge, Rob Hackle, Sean Murray
